xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132553102,imgsize-1167644.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Girl, 11, dies in the River Thames]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132553062.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[In a tragic incident, an 11-year-old girl lost her life after she innocently asked to dip her toes in the River Thames. Two weeks of extensive searching led to the recovery of her body. The inquest determined her death was accidental, resulting from immersion in frigid waters, with no signs of foul play among peers. This devastating loss has left her family heartbroken and in mourning.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/11-year-old-girl-dies-in-river-thames-after-asking-dad-if-she-could-dip-her-toes/articleshow/132553062.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/11-year-old-girl-dies-in-river-thames-after-asking-dad-if-she-could-dip-her-toes/articleshow/132553062.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-22T12:34:40+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132553157,imgsize-119488.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Rising sea levels are making coastal flooding more common around the world; study finds]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132552896.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Coastal flooding is becoming more frequent globally due to rising sea levels.  Extreme sea-level events now occur four times more often than a century ago.  Human-caused warming has amplified the impact of tides and storms.  Natural variations still influence local flood risk across coastlines.  Communities must rethink flood planning based on these changing probabilities.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/rising-sea-levels-are-making-coastal-flooding-more-common-around-the-world-study-finds/articleshow/132552896.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/rising-sea-levels-are-making-coastal-flooding-more-common-around-the-world-study-finds/articleshow/132552896.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-22T12:22:21+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132553008,imgsize-135182.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Colombia planted 880,000 trees across the streets of one city to tackle rising temperatures, and the plantation delivered localised cooling of up to 5°C in shaded areas]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132552891.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/colombia-planted-880000-trees-across-the-streets-of-one-city-to-tackle-rising-temperatures-and-the-plantation-delivered-localised-cooling-of-up-to-5c-in-shaded-areas/articleshow/132552891.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/colombia-planted-880000-trees-across-the-streets-of-one-city-to-tackle-rising-temperatures-and-the-plantation-delivered-localised-cooling-of-up-to-5c-in-shaded-areas/articleshow/132552891.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-22T12:18:41+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132552923,imgsize-2047554.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[AI cracks a mystery from 1939 that mathematicians couldn’t solve for decades]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132552210.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[An artificial intelligence model has aided in identifying a potential solution to an 87-year-old mathematical problem. This development challenges the long-held view of mathematics as a solely human endeavor. Researchers are now exploring AI's potential as a partner in advanced mathematical research. The Jacobian conjecture, proposed in 1939, has resisted decades of human effort. While formal verification is pending, AI's role in creative mathematics is growing.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/ai-cracks-a-mystery-from-1939-that-mathematicians-couldnt-solve-for-decades-the-answer-was-hidden-in-216-characters/articleshow/132552210.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/ai-cracks-a-mystery-from-1939-that-mathematicians-couldnt-solve-for-decades-the-answer-was-hidden-in-216-characters/articleshow/132552210.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-22T12:09:51+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132552830,imgsize-143956.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA['I may be one of the 10 luckiest': Warren Buffett says birth, timing and luck shaped his $147 billion fortune more than investing skill]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132551888.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/i-may-be-one-of-the-10-luckiest-warren-buffett-says-birth-timing-and-luck-shaped-his-147-billion-fortune-more-than-investing-skill/articleshow/132551888.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/i-may-be-one-of-the-10-luckiest-warren-buffett-says-birth-timing-and-luck-shaped-his-147-billion-fortune-more-than-investing-skill/articleshow/132551888.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-22T11:45:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132552126,imgsize-71966.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Why scientists kill 9 million sea lampreys every year in the Great Lakes of America]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132551676.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Invasive sea lampreys, or vampire fish, pose a serious threat to the native fish communities of the Great Lakes. These destructive predators made their way in through canals and now voraciously consume vast amounts of fish annually. Since 1957, the application of TFM has been a cornerstone in eradicating lamprey larvae. However, interruptions in management efforts have caused significant rebounds in lamprey numbers.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/inside-sciences-forbidden-experiment-why-scientists-kill-9-million-sea-lampreys-every-year-in-the-great-lakes-of-america/articleshow/132551676.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/inside-sciences-forbidden-experiment-why-scientists-kill-9-million-sea-lampreys-every-year-in-the-great-lakes-of-america/articleshow/132551676.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-22T11:27:59+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132551775,imgsize-265740.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Nvidia CEO Jensen Huang donates $75 million to preserve the California College of the Arts' legacy as Vanderbilt launches a new college of art, architecture and design]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margi